name: Pipetting
description: Pipetting tools including Single Dilute, Resuspend, Full plate stamping and partial plate stamping

options.name: Transfer: Transfer from multiple containers to a single destination container.

tran_group.description: Choose a source aliquot and designate destination wells.
tran_group.label: Transfer to Single Container

vol.label: Transfer volume
vol.description: Volume to transfer from source well to every destination well in this group.

dest_well.label: Destination Well(s)
dest_well.description: Enter the destination well(s) for the transfer.  Multiple wells can be entered separated by commas.

options.name: Use a container from your inventory

dest_c.label: Use an existing container as a destination
dest_c.description: Use a container in your inventory as a destination.

transfer_name.label: Transfer Well Names
transfer_name.description: Transfer source well names to destination wells.  If a well already has a name, it will not be reassigned.

source_containers.label: Source(s) from Your Inventory
source_containers.description: Select source(s) from your inventory.  This first container in this list will be indexed in the table by '1', the second container will be indexed by '2'.

dest_containers.label: Destination(s) from Your Inventory
dest_containers.description: Select destination(s) from your inventory.  This first container in this list will be indexed in the table by '1', the second container will be indexed by '2'.

transfer_name.label: Transfer Well Names
transfer_name.description: Transfer source well names to destination wells.  If a well already has a name, it will not be reassigned.

options.name: Resuspend: Add a solution to resuspend or dilute a reagent.

diluent.label: Diluent
diluent.description: Choose either a aliquot from your inventory or an offered diluent from the list.

measure_conc.label: Additional Analysis
measure_conc.description: Perform a concentration measurement on each aliquot after resuspension.

options.name: Dilute: Create dilutions in your diluent of choice.

label.label: Container label
label.description: Label for the new container being created. Aliquot name will be derived from the source aliquot name.

diluent.label: Diluent
diluent.description: Choose either a aliquot from your inventory or an offered diluent from the list.

measure_conc.label: Additional Analysis
measure_conc.description: Perform a concentration measurement on each aliquot after dilution.

options.name: Plate stamp: Stamp full plates or individual quadrants to reformat between 96 and 384 plates.

vol.label: Transfer volume
vol.description: Volume to transfer from source plate.

options.name: Use a plate from your inventory

dest_c.label: Use an existing plate as a destination
dest_c.description: Use a plate in your inventory as a destination. Plate must have 96 or 384 wells.

options.name: Row or Column stamp: Stamp a full reactangle of wells to another plate - maintaining the shape.

src_w.label: Source wells - full rows or columes
src_w.description: Source wells have to form a complete rectangle and contain either full rows or full columns

vol.label: Transfer volume
vol.description: Volume to transfer from source plate for every well.

options.name: Use a plate from your inventory

dest_c.label: Use an existing plate as a destination
dest_c.description: Use a plate in your inventory as a destination. Plate must have 96 or 384 wells.

options.name: Cherry pick: Transfer volumes of aliquots from a source plate to a destination plate.

cherry_group.label: Cherry Pick Sets
cherry_group.description: Choose a source and destination plate and upload a well transfer map.

confirm_volume.label: Confirm Source Volumes
confirm_volume.description: Confirm that your source wells have sufficient volume to execute this transfer. If unchecked the protocol will be executed even if some wells do not have the required volume.  Currently, volumes are only confirmed on a single transfer basis and are not cumulatively checked.

w_name.label: Transfer Source Name
w_name.description: Transfer the name of the source well to the destination well.  Note, optional well names designated in the csv will overwrite automatic well naming.

cherry_map.label: Upload Transfer Map
cherry_map.description: Map to transfer from source to destination, according to volumes

options.name: Use a plate from your inventory

dest_c.label: Use an existing plate as a destination
dest_c.description: Use a plate in your inventory as a destination. Plate must have 96 or 384 wells.

cherry_map.label: Upload Transfer Map
cherry_map.description: Map to transfer from source to destination, according to volumes

options.name: Sequentially transfer cherry picked samples to new container.

cherry_map.label: Upload Transfer Map
cherry_map.description: Map of selected wells in source container, transfer will be sequential.

options.name: Consolidate: Transfer volumes from different containers to a destination container.

pick_group.description: Choose a source and destination plate.
pick_group.label: Consolidate Containers

well_vol.description: Indicate how much volume to pipette from each well.
well_vol.label: Volume to consolidate

user_vol.label: Volume
user_vol.description: Volume to be consolidated per well. Limit 2uL per well.

confirm_volume.label: Confirm Source Volumes
confirm_volume.description: Confirm that your source wells have sufficient volume to execute this. Currently, volumes are only confirmed on a single transfer basis and are not cumulatively checked.

dest_well.label: Well Location
dest_well.description: Choose a well destination. A1 indicates the top left well for all plates. If you would like to place your aliquot in the middle of a container: D6 is the middle of a 96 well plate; H12 is the middle of a 384 well plate.

options.name: Use a container from your inventory

dest_c.label: Use an existing container as a destination
dest_c.description: Use a container in your inventory as a destination.

name: Provision
description: Provision a resource from the catalog: https://secure.transcriptic.com/_commercial/kits

cont_type.label: Container type
cont_type.description: Choose the container for the resource to be provisioned into.  If a plate is chosen, all wells in the plate will be filled with the same amount. Additional information about containers can be found at https://developers.transcriptic.com/docs/containers

res_id.label: Resource Id of Resource to be Provisioned

vol.label: Volume to provision
vol.description: Max volumes for containers can be found at https://developers.transcriptic.com/docs/containers

dead_vol.label: Pipette in additional dead volume.
dead_vol.description: Specify whether to provision an additional container specific dead volume. Additional information about dead volumes for containers can be found at https://developers.transcriptic.com/docs/containers
